FAQs
What are the primary requirements to apply to the Medical University of Warsaw?
To apply to the Medical University of Warsaw, you typically need:

A high school diploma or equivalent
Proficiency in English (for programs taught in English)
Strong background in science subjects (Biology, Chemistry, Physics)
Satisfactory scores from recognized international exams (such as SAT, MCAT, or IB)
Passing the university’s entrance exam (if applicable)
Do I need to know Polish to study at the Medical University of Warsaw?
No, many programs at the Medical University of Warsaw are offered in English, especially those aimed at international students. However, knowing Polish can be beneficial for clinical practice and daily life.

